---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const TEAL = '#05d7d1';
const GOLD = '#E8B84B';
---
<Layout title="About — Socially Awkward Media">
  <!-- Banner -->
  <header class="about-banner">
    <span class="well-text">Well,</span>
    <h1 class="about-heading">THIS IS AWKWARD</h1>
    <img
      src="/ollie-full-body.png"
      alt="Ollie the mascot"
      class="ollie"
    />
  </header>
  <!-- Content -->
  <div class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-2xl px-6 pb-16">
    <div
      class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl bg-white shadow-sm"
      style={`border: 2px solid ${TEAL};`}
    >
      <div class="h-2 w-full" style={`background-color: ${GOLD};`}></div>
      <div class="space-y-5 p-8 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        <p class="text-lg font-bold">Some people stumble into creativity. Theia just never stumbled out.</p>
        <p>It started in 2003 with a spark for graphic design — the kind that quietly takes over your brain and never really lets go. By 2006 she'd added web design to the mix, because apparently one creative obsession wasn't enough.</p>
        <p>When Socially Awkward Media came to life in 2022, it didn't stay behind a screen for long. Theia took the brand into the community by organizing and hosting Small Business Saturday — a vendor event dedicated to spotlighting small and home-based businesses. For three years running, that event brought together 100+ vendors and real, enthusiastic community support. Because building up small businesses isn't just a service — it's something she genuinely believes in.</p>
        <p>Today, Socially Awkward Media is exactly where it's always been heading — helping your brand look as good as the work you do.</p>
        <p class="italic" style={`color: ${TEAL}; font-weight: 600;`}>
          No matter what stage of your project you're in — from spark of idea to goal reached — you're in the right place.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
<style>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Caveat:wght@700&display=swap');

  .about-banner {
    position: relative;
    background-color: #05d7d1;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 28px 24px;
    text-align: center;
    overflow: visible;
  }
  .well-text {
    position: absolute;
    top: 10px;
    left: -1px;
    font-family: 'Caveat', cursive;
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #000000;
    z-index: 3;
    line-height: 1;
    transform: rotate(-9deg);
    transform-origin: left center;
  }
  .about-heading {
    font-family: 'Lilita One', cursive;
    color: #ffffff;
    -webkit-text-stroke: 12px #E8B84B;
    paint-order: stroke fill;
    /* Scales down on mobile so the heading fits without horizontal overflow. */
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 100px);
    white-space: nowrap;
    line-height: 1;
    margin: 0;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }
  .ollie {
    position: absolute;
    /* Bottom offset scales with size so his feet hang proportionally below the
       banner edge on mobile too (less negative bottom when he's smaller). */
    bottom: clamp(-25px, -2vw, -14px);
    right: 16px;
    /* Scales with the viewport so he shrinks alongside the banner heading
       (which uses clamp(2rem, 8vw, 100px)). At ≥1300px viewport he's the full
       260px; at narrow mobile viewports he settles at 150px. */
    height: clamp(150px, 20vw, 260px);
    width: auto;
    z-index: 1;
    /* Ollie is decorative; let clicks pass through to the nav links he overlaps. */
    pointer-events: none;
  }
</style>
